As of 19 March 2020, some staff and dependents in the British Embassy have been withdrawn. The British Embassy is closed to visitors but can be contacted by telephone, email or social media.
Most visits to Montenegro are trouble-free.
In early 2020 there were a series of protests which caused occasional disruption and road closures. Public gatherings are now forbidden due to coronavirus. See Political situation
Terrorist attacks in Montenegro canâ€™t be ruled out. See Terrorism
You must register with local police within 24 hours of your arrival in Montenegro. See Registration
Under Montenegrin law you must carry a valid form of ID with you at all times, for example a driving licence, passport or equivalent, otherwise you may be fined. See Local laws and customs
If you are abroad and you need emergency help from the UK government, contact the nearest British embassy, consulate or high commission.
Take out comprehensive travel and medical insurance before you travel.  
